          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1470126509" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3871231957673650413">This is a lovely little novel. It immerses you in two different yet parallel India&apos;s. One of colonial 1923 and the other independence circa 1970s. It is very hard not to draw comparisons with E.M Fosters great novel &quot;A Passage to India&quot; both dealing with the English/Indian cultural clash and the somewhat mystical draw of India on the European character. I have a particular fondness for literature dealing with the follies of Englishman in foreign lands so this slight novel really appealed. My onl</span>
  <span id="freeText3871231957673650413" style="display:none">This is a lovely little novel. It immerses you in two different yet parallel India's. One of colonial 1923 and the other independence circa 1970s. It is very hard not to draw comparisons with E.M Fosters great novel "A Passage to India" both dealing with the English/Indian cultural clash and the somewhat mystical draw of India on the European character. I have a particular fondness for literature dealing with the follies of Englishman in foreign lands so this slight novel really appealed. My only complaint is it does end rather abruptly, I could have read a much longer novel with both Olivia and the Nawab as central characters. </span>
  <a data-text-id="3871231957673650413" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
